UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X99000240
KW  - Adaptive Mesh
KW  - Option valuation
KW  - Lattice models
KW  - Barrier options
KW  - Numerical valuation techniques
AB  - Most derivative securities must be priced by numerical techniques. These models contain “distribution error” and “nonlinearity error”. The Adaptive Mesh Model (AMM) sharply reduces nonlinearity error by grafting one or more small sections of fine high-resolution lattice onto a tree with coarser time and price steps. Three different AMM structures are presented, one for pricing ordinary options, one for barrier options, and one for computing delta and gamma efficiently. The AMM approach can be adapted to a wide variety of contingent claims. For some common problems, accuracy increases by several orders of magnitude with no increase in execution time.
ER  - 

